==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Caret
<hw>Ca"ret</hw> <pr>(k⟦amac⟧"r⟦ecr⟧t <it>or</it> k⟦acr⟧r"⟦ecr⟧t)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>caret</ets> there is wanting, fr.
<ets>carere</ets> to want.]</ety> <def>A mark [^] used by writers and
proof readers to indicate that something is interlined above, or
inserted in the margin, which belongs in the place marked by the
caret.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Caret</ent>⟦br⟧
